  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "But when the flame began to arise up out of the city with a pillar of smoke,.... Fire being set to it by the liers in wait, who had entered it, and who made a large fire, which caused a vast pillar of flame and smoke to arise, which might be seen a great way off: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the Benjamites looked behind them; perhaps at hearing the blowing of the trumpet, and the long sound of that: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and, behold, the flame of the city ascended up to heaven; went upwards, and reached to a great height. ",
        "children": [
